 for bestpractices and # Settings & Preferences Page

## Overview
Build a comprehensive Settings & Preferences page for StudySpark that enables parents to manage account details, child profiles, notification preferences, connected integrations, billing & subscription management, and privacy controls. The page should deliver a friendly, gamified, parent- and child-focused experience with clear visual hierarchy, accessible controls, and robust client-side validation. All frontend code must defensively guard against null/undefined values before using array methods, initialize state with appropriate defaults, and validate API responses. The page should integrate with existing app theming and design system, and be implemented in a modern React + TypeScript stack (Next.js or CRA) with a scalable component structure and clean separation of concerns.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A centralized Settings & Preferences hub where parents can tailor their account, manage their children's profiles, configure notification and privacy preferences, connect / manage third-party integrations (e.g., Google Drive, Dropbox, classroom tools), handle billing and subscription actions, and control privacy-related actions (data export, deletion requests, consent management).

Goals:
- Provide intuitive access to all settings in a single, navigable page with logically grouped sections and collapsible subsections.
- Enable CRUD operations for child profiles (add/edit/delete with confirmation), update parent account details (name, email, password change link), and manage preferences.
- Allow granular notification toggles (email, push, in-app) with per-category controls (study completion, reminders, subscription updates).
- Manage connected integrations with status, re-auth flows, and disconnect options.
- Provide full billing/subscription workflows (view plan, upgrade/downgrade, cancel, view invoices, update payment method).
- Provide privacy controls (data export request, delete data request, consent management) with status indicators and timelines.
- Ensure accessibility (keyboard navigability, aria attributes) and responsive behavior (mobile-first with a polished desktop layout).

UI elements & visual guidance:
- Top section: Avatar/profile header with current parent name, progress toward profile completion, quick actions (Edit profile, Change password, Delete account with confirmation modal).
- Child Profiles: Card grid or list showing each child with avatar, name, age/grade, learning style, and quick actions (Edit, Duplicate, Delete). Include a prominent “Add Child Profile” action.
- Notifications: Section with grouped toggles for Email, Push, and In-app, plus per-category granular toggles (study completion, reminders, subscription updates, etc.). Visualize current status with compact badges.
- Integrations: Card list for Google Drive, Dropbox, and classroom tools with connection status, last sync, and Connect/Disconnect actions.
- Billing & Subscription: Card with current plan, usage/limits, next billing date, ability to upgrade/downgrade, view invoices, update payment method, cancel subscription.
- Privacy Controls: Action items for Data Export Request, Account Deletion Request, and Consent Management (granular toggles for data processing consents). Display status and expected timelines.
- Visual style: Soft pastel peach, muted lavender, and bright tangerine accents; rounded cards, subtle shadows, and playful iconography. Consistent typography and generous whitespace with 16–24px padding, 8–12px gaps, and pill-shaped interactive elements.

API integrations:
- No external API endpoints are required in this task beyond standard app APIs. The page will consume internal API routes for account data, child profiles, notification preferences, integrations, billing data, and privacy actions. Ensure robust client-side validation and safe handling of API responses.

## Components to Build
- SettingsPageContainer
  - Layout wrapper with header, sections, and responsive grid.
- ProfileHeader
  - Displays parent name, profile completion progress, and actions (Edit Profile, Change Password, Delete Account).
- ChildProfilesManager
  - ChildProfileCard: shows name, age, grade, learning style; actions: Edit, Duplicate, Delete.
  - AddChildProfileModal
  - ChildProfileForm (used for add/edit)
- NotificationsPanel
  - NotificationToggleGroup: grouped toggles for Email, Push, In-app
  - CategoryToggleRow: per-category toggles (study completion, reminders, subscription updates)
- IntegrationsPanel
  - IntegrationCard: shows service name, status, lastSync, Connect/Disconnect actions
  - ConnectionStatusBadge
- BillingPanel
  - PlanCard: current plan details, next billing date
  - BillingActions: Upgrade/Downgrade, Cancel
  - InvoicesList: list of invoices
  - PaymentMethodSection: update payment method
- PrivacyPanel
  - DataExportButton
  - DataDeletionButton
  - ConsentManagementPanel: per-processor/privacy consent toggles
- ConfirmationModal
  - Reusable for destructive actions (Delete account, Delete child, Cancel subscription)
- ConfirmationToast/Alert
  - Minimal feedback UI for actions
- SkeletonLoader / EmptyState components
- Shared UI:
  - PillToggle, Switch, Button, Input, Select, Card, Avatar, Badge, Tooltip
- Utilities
  - apiClient wrappers with safe null handling
  - validators for email, password strength, age, etc.
  - helpers for safe array handling: mapGuarded, toArraySafe

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Architecture:
  - React + TypeScript with functional components and hooks.
  - State management using React Context or lightweight state (no global store required) for user session and settings data.
  - All array operations guarded: use (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [], etc.
  - Default state shapes:
    - useState<ChildProfile[]>([]) for child profiles
    - useState<NotificationSettings>({ email: { enabled: false, ... }, push: {...}, inApp: {...} })
    - useState<Integration[]> ([]) for integrations
    - useState<BillingInfo> with defaults
    - useState<PrivacySettings> with defaults
- Data handling:
  - Fetch initial data on mount with safe null checks: const profiles = Array.isArray(data?.profiles) ? data.profiles : []
  - Use data ?? [] for Supabase-like results if applicable
  - Validate API responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels, proper heading hierarchy, keyboard navigable controls
- UI Behavior:
  - Collapsible sections with smooth transitions
  - Cards with hover/active states
  - Form validation with inline messages
  - Debounced search/filter where appropriate (e.g., child search)
- Performance:
  - Lazy load heavy sections if needed
  - Efficient re-renders by memoizing list items
- Validation & safety:
  - Never call array methods on potentially null/undefined values—guard with (profiles ?? []).map(...)
  - Ensure all API responses are validated before using fields
- Routing & navigation:
  - If using Next.js, pages/settings.tsx with proper routing and server/client data fetching where appropriate
- State initialization:
  - Use proper defaults: useState<ChildProfile[]>([]), useState<Invoice[]>([]), etc.
- Styling:
  - Consume existing design system tokens and components
  - Ensure responsive layout with grid/flex that adapts to mobile

### Backend
- APIs to implement or consume (mocked in prompt if not present):
  - GET /api/settings/parent - fetch parent account info
  - PUT /api/settings/parent - update parent name/email
  - POST /api/settings/child - create child profile
  - PUT /api/settings/child/{id} - update child profile
  - DELETE /api/settings/child/{id} - delete child profile (with server-side soft delete)
  - GET /api/settings/notifications - fetch notification preferences
  - PUT /api/settings/notifications - update preferences
  - GET /api/settings/integrations - list connected integrations
  - POST /api/settings/integrations/{provider} - connect
  - DELETE /api/settings/integrations/{provider} - disconnect
  - GET /api/billing - fetch plan, invoices, payment methods
  - POST /api/billing/change-plan - upgrade/downgrade
  - POST /api/billing/cancel - cancel subscription
  - GET /api/privacy/exports - data export requests
  - POST /api/privacy/export - request data export
  - POST /api/privacy/delete - request data deletion
  - GET /api/privacy/consents - consent statuses
  - PUT /api/privacy/consents - update consents
- Data modeling (schema suggestions):
  - ParentAccount: id, name, email, avatarUrl, profileCompletion
  - ChildProfile: id, name, age, grade, learningStyle, avatarUrl, preferences
  - NotificationSettings: email: { enabled, categories }, push: { enabled, categories }, inApp: { enabled, categories }
  - Integration: id, provider, connected, lastSync, metadata
  - BillingInfo: planId, planName, price, nextBillingDate, invoices[]
  - Invoice: id, date, amount, status, pdfUrl
  - PrivacySettings: dataExportConsent, deletionConsent, dataRetention, dataSharing
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation mirrors frontend validations
  - Ensure sensitive actions require confirmation

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - SettingsPage fetches all necessary data on mount.
  - User interactions trigger API calls; optimistic UI updates with rollback on error.
  - After significant changes (billing, deletion, account changes), show confirmation dialogs and success/failure toasts.
- Error handling:
  - Centralized error handling with user-friendly messages
  - Re-authentication prompts on 401s if needed
- Consistency:
  - Use the same data shapes and type guards across components
  - All arrays guarded (e.g., profiles, invoices) before mapping

## User Experience Flow
- Step 1: User lands on Settings & Preferences Page. Page loads: Parent profile header shows name and completion; a progress bar indicates overall setup status.
- Step 2: Parent edits account details via ProfileHeader → opens ProfileForm modal or inline editor. Validate and save; show success toast.
- Step 3: Parent adds a Child Profile via Add Child button → fills out form (name, age, grade, learning style) → saves; newly added profile appears in grid with proper avatars.
- Step 4: Parent customizes Notifications → toggles for Email/Push/In-app; per-category preferences; save changes and see live status badges.
- Step 5: Parent manages Integrations → connect or disconnect Google Drive, Dropbox, etc.; view last sync status.
- Step 6: Parent reviews Billing & Subscription → view current plan, upgrade/downgrade, view invoices, update payment method, or cancel with confirmation.
- Step 7: Parent accesses Privacy Controls → request data export, request deletion, adjust consent toggles; monitor status.
- Step 8: All changes show consistent feedback via toasts and, where applicable, in-page status indicators and inline validation messages.
- Step 9: All actions guarded with confirmations for destructive actions (delete account/child/profile cancellation).

## Technical Specifications

Data Models:
- ParentAccount: id, name, email, avatarUrl, profileCompletion
- ChildProfile: id, parentId, name, age, grade, learningStyle, avatarUrl, preferences
- NotificationSettings: id, parentId, channels: { email, push, inApp }, categories: { studyCompleted, reminders, subscriptionUpdates }
- Integration: id, parentId, provider, connected, lastSync, metadata
- BillingInfo: id, parentId, planId, planName, price, nextBillingDate, invoices[]
- Invoice: id, billingPeriodStart, billingPeriodEnd, amount, currency, status, pdfUrl
- PrivacySettings: id, parentId, dataExportConsent, deletionConsent, consents

API Endpoints:
- GET /api/settings/parent
- PUT /api/settings/parent
- GET /api/settings/child
- POST /api/settings/child
- PUT /api/settings/child/{id}
- DELETE /api/settings/child/{id}
- GET /api/settings/notifications
- PUT /api/settings/notifications
- GET /api/settings/integrations
- POST /api/settings/integrations/{provider}
- DELETE /api/settings/integrations/{provider}
- GET /api/billing
- POST /api/billing/change-plan
- POST /api/billing/cancel
- GET /api/billing/invoices
- GET /api/privacy/exports
- POST /api/privacy/export
- POST /api/privacy/delete
- GET /api/privacy/consents
- PUT /api/privacy/consents

Security:
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth session required; protected routes
